== Clocking ==

A quartz crystal resonator on the N64 motherboard supplies the X'tal1 (X1) reference clock to the clock synthesizer (U7 or U17<ref>Early boards use the 8-pin Macronix MX8330MC at U7; later revisions substitute with equivalent MX9911MC. "Funtastic"-era and later models consolidate U7 and U15 into a single 14-pin MX8350 synthesizer at U17.</ref>) in order to generate the VI clock frequency (VCLK).

=== Crystal Frequency Derivation ===

Each regional broadcast standard defines a horizontal line frequency (<math>f_H</math>), from which the chrominance subcarrier frequency (<math>f_{SC}</math>) is derived as a fixed rational multiple. X1 is defined as 4 × <math>f_{SC}</math>.

